"Start party. GOOD NEWS: permit requirements temporarily lifted for parties"
"Your party already has a Party Space going."
"You must be in a party to activate. Didn't you read the instructions?"

"1. Assemble the desired group of party attendees by clicking on Glitches in person or in chat, and selecting "Invite to Party" to invite.

2. Continue until your party has reached Maximum Fun Capacity Level. While waiting for party pack activation, the party chat channel can be used for smalltalk and metaphorical icebreaking. 

3. Once Party Participants are assembled, activate party pack. Do this by clicking 'Activate' on party pack. 

4. Every guest in party chat will be sent an offer to create a teleportation portal that will take them directly your private party space, regardless of their current location. Party Participants have a limited time to join, so ensure everyone is ready to party. 

5. PARTY HARD. 

<font size="10">SMALL PRINT: 
* A single-activation party pack gives a party of limited duration. To extend party length, insert currants into the machine inside your private party space. CORRECT CURRANTS ONLY. NO CHANGE GIVEN. Parties limited to "

" participants.\n* Please note, due to physical funness capacity, individuals can only participate in one party at a time.\n* The giants and their representatives are not responsible for the level of fun experienced at parties. No refunds for bad parties.</font>"
